        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Voiceprint",
                  "textSize": "heading-two"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "italic": true,
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "italic": true,
                  "text": "Voiceprint: Speech, Language, Communications Technology, and Literary Arts in a Changing World "
                },
                {
                  "text": "was a University of Alberta campus radio show produced by Jars Balan and production assistant Terri Wynnyk. It aired on CKUA from 1980 to 1983 (UAlberta Archives, No. 88-47). This interdisciplinary show covered a blend of communications theory, literary arts, and politics. \n"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Episode topics included Canadian English & Literature, Speech & Its Characteristics, Women's Language & Literature, and more.\n"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Read more in Chelsea Miya's SpokenWeb UAlberta ",
                  "italic": true
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "url": "https://spokenweb.ualberta.ca/spokenweb-ualberta/exhibits/voiceprint/",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "article on Voiceprint",
                      "italic": true
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "italic": true
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "italic": true
                },
                {
                  "text": "Celebrations",
                  "textSize": "heading-two"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "italic": true,
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Celebrations ",
                  "italic": true
                },
                {
                  "text": "was a University of Alberta campus radio show produced by Jars Balan, which aired on CKUA from 1983-84. This show consisted of a year-long series of interviews between host Jars Balan and past Writers-In-Residence, who had gathered in Edmonton to celebrate the university’s 75th anniversary."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Writers who were interviewed include Matt Cohen, Dorothy Livesay, Margaret Atwood, and more."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Read more in Ariel Kroon's SpokenWeb UAlberta ",
                  "italic": true
                },
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "url": "https://spokenwebalberta.github.io/spokenweb-ualberta/exhibits/celebrations/",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "text": "article on Celebrations",
                      "italic": true
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "italic": true
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "\n",
                  "italic": true
                },
                {
                  "text": "Paper Tygers",
                  "textSize": "heading-two"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Paper Tygers",
                  "italic": true
                },
                {
                  "text": " was a University of Alberta campus radio show produced by Jars Balan, which aired on CKUA in the 1980s. This show discussed the craft of writing, with episode topics including Creative Writing, the Writer & Human Rights, and Poetry: The Sullen Art or Craft.\n"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
